# <type>(optional scope): (If applied, this commit will...) <subject> (Max 50 char)
# |<----  Using a Maximum Of 50 Characters  ---->|


# Explain why this change is being made
# |<----   Try To Limit Each Line to a Maximum Of 72 Characters   ---->|


# Provide links or keys to any relevant tickets, articles or other resources
# Example: ISSUE: #23

# --- COMMIT END ---
#  Revert
#    If the commit reverts a previous commit, it should begin with "revert: "
#    followed by the header of the reverted commit.
#    In the body it should say: "This reverts commit <hash>."
#    where the hash is the SHA of the commit being reverted.
#    Example:
#      revert: let us never again speak of the noodle incident
#
#      Refs: 676104e, a215868
#
#  Type
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code change)
#    chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#    major    (breaking change)
#    perf     (code change that improves performance)
#    build    (changes that affect the build system or external dependencies (gulp, broccoli, npm, etc))
#    ci       (changes to our CI configuration files and scripts)
#
#  Scope
#    MAY be provided after a type.
#    MUST consist of a noun describing a section of the codebase surrounded by parenthesis, e.g., fix(parser):
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Subject
#    Use the imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes"
#    Don't capitalize the first letter
#    No dot (.) at the end
#    Breaking changes MUST be indicated by a ! immediately before the :
#
#  Body
#    Separate subject from body with a blank line.
#    Use the body to explain what and why vs. how.
#    Can use multiple lines with "-" for bullet points in body.
#    Use the imperative, present tense: "change" not "changed" nor "changes".
#    Include the motivation for the change and contrast this with previous behavior.
#    SHALL be used to describe the breaking change.
#
#  Footer
#    Contains any information about Breaking Changes.
#    Contains references to issues that this commit Closes e.g. Closes #123, #245, #992
#    Breaking Changes should start with the word BREAKING CHANGE: with a space or two newlines.
#    The rest of the commit message is then used for this.
#    If ! is used, BREAKING CHANGE: MAY be omitted.
#    One or more footers MAY be provided one blank line after the body.
#    Each footer MUST consist of a word token, followed by either a :<space> or <space>#
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# For more information about this template, check out
# https://github.com/angular/angular/blob/22b96b9/CONTRIBUTING.md#-commit-message-guidelines
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/
# https://gist.github.com/creeperyang/821e31f7bbe3d3c7659c608ceae0f629
